<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>@ViewBag.Title - My ASP.NET Application</title>
    @Styles.Render("~/Content/css")
    @Scripts.Render("~/bundles/modernizr")

</head>
<body>
  <div class="navbar navbar-inverse navbar-fixed-top">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="navbar-header">
        <button type="button" class="navbar-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-target=".navbar-collapse">
          <span class="icon-bar"></span>
          <span class="icon-bar"></span>
          <span class="icon-bar"></span>
        </button>
        @Html.ActionLink("Application name", "Index", "Home", new { area = "" }, new { @class = "navbar-brand" })
      </div>
      <div class="navbar-collapse collapse">
        <ul class="nav navbar-nav">
          <li>@Html.ActionLink("Home", "Index", "Home")</li>
          <li>@Html.ActionLink("About", "Index", "About")</li>
          <li>@Html.ActionLink("Care", "Index", "Care")</li>
          <li>@Html.ActionLink("Events", "Index", "Events")</li>
          <li>@Html.ActionLink("Files", "Index", "Files")</li>
          <li>@Html.ActionLink("Contact", "Index", "Contact")</li>
        </ul>
        @Html.Partial("_LoginPartial")
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="container body-content">
    <h2>IMPORTANT:</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Don't touch the connection strings or the database - if you break it you <strong>will die a slow and painful death</strong></li>
      <li>When you make changes to a model remember to go to the PM console and type:<strong>Add-Migration sampletextname</strong>. After thats done type <strong>Update-Database</strong> to finalize your changes.</li>
      <li>plz write neat code</li>
    </ol>
    <h2>To-Do still</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>File Uploading for <strong>home page</strong>. Either create a field in the Index.cs model to handle images (for example see Files.Cs and FilesController.cs). Or add a relationship with the Files Model.</li>
      <li>Many-to-Many file uploading on Events page. Only links to .pdfs, .docs, etc. No image previews</li>
      <li>Change colour of old event cards to grey</li>
      <li>File uploading for the Care page(Model = Program.cs)</li>
      <li>Add all this functionality, then move on to authorization/authentication</li>
    </ul>
    @RenderBody()
    <hr />
    <footer>
      <p>&copy; @DateTime.Now.Year - My ASP.NET Application</p>
    </footer>
  </div>

  @Scripts.Render("~/bundles/jquery")
  @Scripts.Render("~/bundles/bootstrap")
  @RenderSection("scripts", required: false)
</body>
</html>
